node.text:
Celebrate with @unworldoceansday and @oceanic.global starting today at 10 am EST. 
When the world feels like
it’s at a standstill, it’s important to remember what keeps it spinning. Our ocean is our life source, supporting us & every other organism on earth. Celebrate @UNWorldOceansDay
on June 8th with @UnitedNations
and @Oceanic.Global
to learn what thought leaders around the world are doing to protect the ocean and how you can be part of the solution. Featured ocean voices include @caradelevingne,
@fatoumata_diawara__, @fcousteau, @c.syresmith, @jackharries, @thegreatbubblebarrier, @codysimpson, @oceanx, @alessandraambrosio and
more! 
This all-digital event is
free and open to all online. Learn more & register:  UNWorldOceansDay.org/2020

Lunch time 🐢

🎥 @livsoceanworld: "So lucky to be a part of the underwater world and showing people these absolutely amazing creatures! Since the already have so much against them let’s not add to their fight! Remember to reduce reuse and recycle ♻️ and take care of what we throw away. That way the next generation will also get to experience swimming in the ocean with these beauties!"
#DiscoverOcean

node.text:
Taricaya turtle release! 🐢💚
These turtles have suffered greatly due to lack of human conscience, the effects of gold mining and the contamination of their habitat. Now these little ones have a new opportunity thanks to the Taricaya Turtle Repopulation Project! @taricaya.eco.reserve

Video by @mikaelaswildlife & @taricaya.eco.reserve

Mikaela said: “Every night we go out searching for their eggs on the beach before they can be taken for food, incubate them at camp and then release them back into the wild where they belong!” 🙏🏽
#DiscoverOcean
